Abstract

This project implements a user registration system using Spring Boot and MongoDB.
When a user submits their details through a frontend form, the data is stored in a MongoDB database and a confirmation email is automatically sent to the user.

Objective

The main objectives of this project are:
To create a user using an HTML form.
To store user data in MongoDB.
To send an email notification after successful registration.

Technologies Used

Layer:	Technology
Backend:	Spring Boot
Database:	MongoDB
Frontend:	HTML, CSS
Email Service:	Spring Mail
Build Tool: 	Maven

Architecture Flow:

User submits form from frontend.
Backend API receives and processes the data.
MongoDB stores user information.
Email service sends confirmation mail.
Response is returned to the frontend.